<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7835f8f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s102"><num value="102">§ 102.</num><heading> Military departments</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The military departments are:</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I66" role="listItem" class="indent3 firstIndent-1">The Department of the Army.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I66" role="listItem" class="indent3 firstIndent-1">The Department of the Navy.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I66" role="listItem" class="indent3 firstIndent-1">The Department of the Air Force.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb7835f90-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/554">Pub. L. 89–554</ref>, <date date="1966-09-06">Sept. 6, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/378">80 Stat. 378</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb7835f91-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idb7835f92-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The section is supplied to avoid the necessity for defining “military departments” each time it is used in this title. See <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s101/7">section 101(7) of title 10</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
